He then entered the Saint Petersburg Conservatory as an unregistered student in September 1906 and studied under Nikolai Rimsky-Korsakov and Alexander Glazunov.
He left the conservatory in May 1907, taught at Moscow Conservatory and conducted at the Bolshoi Theatre.
